The paper deals with the computational complexity of the Balanced Connected Subgraph problem on various geometric intersection graphs, such as interval, circular-arc, permutation, unit-disk, and outer-string graphs. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the design of polynomial-time algorithms and FPT algorithms, which suggests that it may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), and Graph Theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the NP-hardness of the problem on certain graph classes, indicating that it may also belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
